<p>Regarding SELECT INTO in SQL Server</p>  <p>The following throw an error <code>Incorrect syntax near ')'.</code></p>  <pre><code>SELECT * INTO Sales.MyTable FROM  (SELECT TOP(100) * FROM Sales.Customer) </code></pre>  <p>The following will pass</p>  <pre><code>With tempCust AS ( SELECT TOP(100) * FROM Sales.Customer ) SELECT * INTO Sales.MyTable FROM tempCust </code></pre>  <p>What is the rule behind that ?</p>